-- South African Rail Operator Buys First Chinese Locomotives
-- B y   J a c o   V i s s e r
-- 2012-10-22T11:03:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-22/south-african-rail-operator-buys-first-chinese-locomotives.html
Transnet SOC Ltd., the South African
state-owned rail operator, is making its first-ever purchase of
electric locomotives from  China .  The Johannesburg-based company said it will pay 2.6 billion
rand ($301 million) to buy 95 locomotives from CSR Zhuzhou
Electric Locomotive Co. The first 10 locomotives will be built
in China, with the remainder being assembled in South Africa,
according to a statement released by the rail operator.  Transnet will buy 1,064 new locomotives for about 35
billion rand over the next seven years, Malusi Gigaba, the
public enterprises minister, told reporters today in  Pretoria ,
the capital.  The rail operator plans to invest 110 billion rand in new
equipment over the period to increase its freight volume from
201 million metric tons to 350 million tons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
